title: A view from the Ukrainian town bearing the brunt of Russia's grinding assault
description: Richard Engel reports from Bakhmut, which is being shelled relentlessly by President Vladimir Putin's forces.

title: El Salvador vows to keep gang crackdown as citizens support safer streets
description: El Salvador’s state of emergency to combat gangs, which has widespread public support, will be maintained, the country’s security minister said.

title: Captain of Thai ‘cave boys’ soccer team dies in the U.K.
description: One of 12 boys dramatically rescued after two weeks trapped in a flooded cave in Thailand in 2018 has died in Britain where he was attending a soccer academy, his former teacher said Wednesday.

title: Scottish leader Sturgeon resigns after 8 years
description: Scottish First Minister Nicola Sturgeon on Wednesday announced her intention to resign, saying that part of serving in politics is knowing when it is time to make way for someone else.

title: The city that didn't collapse: How Erzin became a haven from Turkey's earthquake
description: Death and destruction surround Erzin, but the city in Turkey’s Hatay province suffered no deaths and saw no buildings collapse in last week’s earthquake, residents and officials say, as the fallout focuses on construction codes.

title: Unlikely that Kim Jong Un’s daughter is being groomed as successor, South Korea says
description: South Korea said it’s too early to know whether the recently unveiled daughter of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un is being groomed as her father’s successor.

title: Kidnapped New Zealand pilot shown in Indonesia rebels’ photos and videos
description: Separatist rebels in Indonesia’s Papua province released photos and videos of a man they said is the pilot from New Zealand whom they took hostage last week.

title: China expresses support for Iran amid Western pressure
description: Chinese leader Xi Jinping expressed support for Iran during a visit by President Ebrahim Raisi as Tehran tries to expand relations with Beijing and Moscow.

title: 4 men arrested in the U.S. in assassination of Haitian President Jovenel Moïse
description: Four men were arrested in Florida on Tuesday in connection with the assassination of Haitian President Jovenel Moïse, officials said.

title: Rescue workers in Turkey and Syria still finding miracles in earthquake aftermath
description: Rescue workers are still finding survivors in the rubble from the massive earthquakes that impacted millions in Turkey and Syria. NBC News’ Matt Bradley has more details on the aftermath.

title: Ukrainian forces running low on ammunition
description: Ukrainian forces are running low on ammunition as NATO warns that Western allies cannot provide it fast enough. Meanwhile, Russia still produces ammunition for its Soviet-era tanks and has huge reserves. NBC News’ Richard Engel has more on the ongoing conflict.
